article.description: Jack Forrest scored a career-high 20 points and Columbia beat Division III Mount St. Vincent 86-56 on Thursday night in its final nonconference game of the season.
article.headline: Forrest lifts Columbia past Mount Saint Vincent 86-56
article.linkText: Forrest lifts Columbia past Mount Saint Vincent 86-56
article.story: NEW YORK -- Jack Forrest scored a career-high 20 points and Columbia beat Division III Mount St. Vincent 86-56 on Thursday night in its final nonconference game of the season. Mike Smith scored 14 points and made five assists for the Lions (5-11), who never trailed and led 41-20 at halftime. Jake Killingsworth scored 13 points and Tai Bibbs had 10. Randy Brumant grabbed 11 rebounds and Joseph Smoyer blocked four shots. Raiquis Harris scored 13 points and Kelvin Turner-Harris added 12 for the Dolphins, who shot 32% from the floor. Dorian Robinson scored 10 points and had eight rebounds. Columbia faces Cornell at home next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
